article.headline: N. Arizona 83, E. Washington 74
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Gabe Rogers scored 29 points and Cameron Jones added 27 as Northern Arizona rallied from an 18-point deficit to beat Eastern Washington 83-74 on Wednesday night. Rogers and Jones combined for 40 of the Lumberjacks' 56 second-half points, helping Northern Arizona (15-10, 7-6 Big Sky) shoot 72 percent from the floor after halftime. Glen Dean had a career-high 31 points for the Eagles (8-17, 5-8). No one else scored in double figures for Eastern Washington, which dropped to 1-13 on the road. Rogers hit 10-of-16 shots, including all three of his 3-point attempts, in finishing two points shy of his career high. Jones was 8 of 12 from the floor, 11 for 14 from the free-throw line and grabbed eight rebounds. Shane Johannsen had 12 points, nine rebounds and four blocks for the Lumberjacks, who improved to 10-1 at home.
